text: @FedExHelp @FedEx Why do you even bother offering tracking information when it’s useless?

@thecorncolonel @thecorncolonel  Hello, my name is Rebecca. I apologize for any inconvenience you have experienced.  Would you like help with tracking your package?  Please DM your name, address, tracking number, and phone number. 
Thank you.

@FedExHelp I can track it. It leaves Grove City, OH. Then it arrives at Grove City, OH. From there, it ships to Grove City, OH and then arrives later at Grove City, OH. 

If I lived in Grove City, OH, I have no doubt you’d be very efficient.
@FedExHelp for the love of everything, what are you all doing?  Do I need to drive to Grove City and get my package? Just tell me. https://t.co/zeNNfKsNDk
@thecorncolonel Hi, this is Dolores. May I look into this for you? Please DM your name, address, city, state, zip code, tracking number, phone number, and email address. https://t.co/7vnSkvqx3r

@FedEx @FedExOffice @FedExHelp Cannot offer explanation to why a package is being shipped back and forth between the same facilities repeatedly. DHL is an improvement over this company.  It’s 2018 and they’re the only company that can’t get package tracking right. Kudos.
